{
  "text": "Then each entity is on a path that leads to the one destination. This is like many, many roads which travel through many, many places but eventually merge into one large center. This is correct, but some water wanting in depth of description more applicable would be the thought that each entity contains within it all of the densities and subdensities of the octave, so that in each entity no matter whither its choices lead it. Its great internal blueprint is one with all others. Thusly, its experiences will fall into the patterns of the journey back to the original logos. This is done through free will, but the materials from which choices can be made are one blueprint.",
